{
  "_note": "Affix pools v1. D2 affix model (prefix/suffix, ilvl-gated tiers). 'weight' makes selection non-uniform; 'stat' = engine key. Each TIER carries its own escalating 'name' \u2014 the engine names a drop '<prefix> <base> <suffix>' from the rolled tiers (e.g. 'Merciless Reaping Scythe of the Salamander'). Tier-name ladders adapted from the user's ARPG affix dataset, remapped to Deepgilt's 5 stats (might/finesse/vigor/wit/wyrd) + 6 elements (steel/ember/rime/galv/rot/wither); names that were D&D Product Identity (e.g. 'of the Drow') were dropped; only generic/public-domain flavor kept. Not SRD content \u2014 no attribution required. EXCLUSION: optional 'group' = D2 affix group; two affixes sharing a group never co-roll. When omitted the engine uses 'stat' as the group (so same-stat affixes are mutually exclusive). Optional 'req_alvl' overrides the default required affix-level (= lowest tier ilvl).",
